definitions.definition: Having its own or a single nature or character throughout, as in colour, composition, etc., without addition or change; of the same kind ; unmixed.
examples: a self bow: one made from a single piece of wood
a self flower or plant: one which is wholly of one colour

definitions.definition: Of or relating to any molecule, cell, or tissue of an organism 's own (belonging to the self ), as opposed to a foreign ( nonself ) molecule, cell, or tissue (for example, infective , allogenic , or xenogenic ).
